------variables means
n PL/SQL, a variable is named storage location that stores a value of a particular data type. 
The value of the variable changes through the program.
Before using a variable, you must declare it in the declaration section of a block.


-----The syntax for a variable declaration is as follows:

variable_name datatype [NOT NULL] [:= initial_value];



DECLARE
    customer_group VARCHAR2(100) := 'mango';
BEGIN
    customer_group := 'Grapes';
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(customer_group);
END;


DECLARE 
   product_name VARCHAR2(100) DEFAULT 'tv';
BEGIN 
   NULL; 
END;
